info.title: Datarotonde API
info.description:
This API is used to get data from the CDM.

OData

All operations support OData querying. For more information on valid values for the OData parameters on the operations, see OData documentation

Full querystring example: ?$top=5&$skip=10&$select=AccountNumber,Name,BusinessAddress&$filter=Name eq 'Some name'&$expand=BusinessAddress&$orderby=AccountNumber

Filter operations list can be found in the OData filter operation protocol specification. To filter on child objects use the all or any lambda operators in the filter (using a filter on the $expand operator will not filter the parent objects returned but only filter the child objects returned for a parent object).

Example:
$expand=BusinessAddress($filter=PostalCode eq '1111AA' and HouseNumber eq 1) will return all Business but will only expand BusinessAddress child objects that match the filter.
$filter=BusinessAddress/any(d:d/PostalCode eq '1111AA' and d/HouseNumber eq 1) will return only Business objects that have at least one BusinessAddress that matches the filter.

When using the all lambda operator remember that an empty collection will return true. Filter out empty collections by using an empty any lambda.

Example: $filter=BusinessAddress/any() and BusinessAddress/all(d:d/PostalCode eq '1111AA')

The service does not support any of the following query options $search, $format, $schemaversion, $count.

Deprecation notices

API Versions

  • Business
    • BusinessNumber

Release Notes

Search all employees with optional OData queries
get.description:
Example call with OData filters:
https://serviceurl/employees?$filter=EmployeeNumber%20eq%209360&$select=BinNumber,FirstName,Surname
By default no accountancy data is included. To retrieve Accountancy with results use:
https://serviceurl/employees?$expand=Accountancy
